TY  - JOUR
AU  - Beaulieu, J. Joseph
AU  - MacKie-Mason, Jeffrey K.
AU  - Miron, Jeffrey A.
T1  - Why Do Countries and Industries with Large Seasonal Cycles Also Have Large Business Cycles?*
PY  - 1992
Y1  - 1992/05/01
DO  - 10.2307/2118484
JO  - The Quarterly Journal of Economics
JA  - Q J Econ
VL  - 107
IS  - 2
SP  - 621
EP  - 656
SN  - 0033-5533
AB  - We show that there is a strong, positive correlation across countries and industries between the standard deviation of the seasonal component and the standard deviation of the nonseasonal component of aggregate variables. After documenting this stylized fact, we discuss possible explanations and develop a model that generates our empirical finding. The main feature of the model is that firms endogenously choose their degree of technological flexibility as a function of the amounts of seasonal and nonseasonal variation in demand. Although this model is intended to be illustrative, we find evidence supporting one of its key empirical implications.
Y2  - 3/25/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.2307/2118484
ER  - 



