TY  - JOUR
AU  - Anton, James J.
AU  - Yao, Dennis A.
T1  - Coordination in Split Award Auctions*
PY  - 1992
Y1  - 1992/05/01
DO  - 10.2307/2118486
JO  - The Quarterly Journal of Economics
JA  - Q J Econ
VL  - 107
IS  - 2
SP  - 681
EP  - 707
SN  - 0033-5533
AB  - We analyze split award procurement auctions in which a buyer divides full production between two suppliers or awards all production to a single supplier, and suppliers have private cost information. An intriguing feature of split awards is that the equilibrium bids are implicitly coordinated. Because a split award price is the sum of offered split prices, each supplier can unilaterally veto a split award by bidding very high for the split. The need to coordinate is reflected in a split price that does not vary with private information. We also explore conditions under which split award auctions may be preferred to winner-take-all auctions.
Y2  - 3/25/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.2307/2118486
ER  - 



